President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation recognizing National Hunting and Fishing Day in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of hunting and fishing in American society, the economy, and conservation efforts. It mentions that millions of Americans participate in these activities, contributing billions of dollars to the economy each year. The proclamation also emphasizes the role of hunters and anglers as conservationists and stewards of the environment. President Trump reaffirms his commitment to keeping lands and waterways open for these activities and encourages Americans to appreciate and support the contributions of hunters and anglers.